Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (190 degrees C).

Combine @Parmesan cheese{1⁄2%cup}, @paprika{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, @parsley{1%teaspoon}, and @pepper{1⁄2%teaspoon} in a flat shallow dish; mix well.

Coat each pork chop with @olive oil{2%tablespoons}. Dredge both sides of each chop in the Parmesan mixture and set on a plate.

Place 2 chops in the basket of the air fryer and cook for 10 minutes; flipping halfway through cook time. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes. Repeat with remaining chops.

Served hot and enjoy!

For easy cleanup and less mess, mix the Parmesan mixture in a long flat-lidded plastic to-go container. Place one chop in at a time, snap the lid, and shake. Transfer to the plate and repeat with remaining chops. Perfectly coated chops every single time!